  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(27) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then the priests the Levites.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And the Levitical priests;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " not any irregular ministrants. Some Hebrew MSS., the LXX., Syriac, and the Vulg. read, “And the priests and the Levites”: but comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 23:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And their voice was heard.—The priestly blessing was a prayer that Jehovah would bless. (See Numbers 6:22-27.) That the prayer was heard on the present occasion, the writer infers from the progress of reform among the people, and the wonderful deliverance from Assyria, as related in the ensuing chapters.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And their voice was heard.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The priestly blessing was a prayer that Jehovah would bless. (See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 6:22-27",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) That the prayer was heard on the present occasion, the writer infers from the progress of reform among the people, and the wonderful deliverance from Assyria, as related in the ensuing chapters.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Their prayer came up.—Entered into His holy dwelling (comp. Isaiah 18:6) into the heavens. Notice the characteristic omission of the sacred Name.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Their prayer came up.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
